                        "title": "Authorization header leak in ssrf_filter via cross-host redirect leads to credential theft and unauthorized access",
                        "substate": "resolved",
                        "url": "https://hackerone.com/reports/3642600",
                        "disclosed_at": "2026-04-15T20:43:58.628Z",
                        "report_generated_content": {
                            "id": "Z2lkOi8vaGFja2Vyb25lL1JlcG9ydEdlbmVyYXRlZENvbnRlbnQvODY0Ng==",
                            "hacktivity_summary": "A vulnerability was discovered in the `ssrf_filter` library. The vulnerability allowed an attacker-controlled redirect target to receive credentials that were intended only for the original request origin. This was possible because `ssrf_filter` followed redirects by rebuilding each redirected request from the original request options, including the `Authorization` header. As a result, sensitive state such as bearer tokens was forwarded across cross-host redirects, leading to credential theft and unauthorized access.",
